            <!-- Category 3: Strength Training Fundamentals -->
            <div class="faq-category faq-hidden">
                <h2 class="faq-category-title">Fundamentals: Understanding Strength Training</h2>
                <div class="faq-list">
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What is strength training and how does it differ from cardio?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Strength training aims to build muscles using resistance (weights, bands, bodyweight). Cardio targets cardiovascular endurance. Both are complementary and AIVancePro helps you combine them based on your goals.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Why is strength training important for health?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Strength training strengthens bones, improves metabolism, reduces injury risk, improves posture and contributes to mental health. It is recommended at all ages.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What is the difference between hypertrophy, strength and endurance?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Hypertrophy targets muscle size (8-12 reps), maximal strength works with heavy loads (1-5 reps), and muscular endurance uses lighter loads with many repetitions (15+). AIVancePro adjusts the parameters based on your goal.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            How many times per week should I train?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Generally 3 to 5 times per week for optimal results. The AI coach adjusts frequency and volume based on your availability and recovery.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What is progressive overload and why is it important?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Progressive overload means gradually increasing weight, reps or volume to keep making progress. It is the fundamental principle of progression in strength training. AIVancePro tracks your progress and helps you apply this principle.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Can you lose fat with strength training?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, strength training increases your basal metabolic rate and burns calories during and after your workout. Combined with proper nutrition, it is one of the most effective ways to lose fat.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Do I need to lift heavy to see results?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Not necessarily. Consistency, proper technique and progressive overload matter more than absolute weight. Even with moderate loads, you can achieve excellent results.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What equipment do I need to get started?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">No equipment is required! You can start with bodyweight exercises. To progress faster, a pair of adjustable dumbbells is a great investment. AIVancePro adapts to whatever equipment you have.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What are the most important muscle groups to work?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">A balanced program should cover all major groups: chest, back, shoulders, arms, legs and abs. The AI coach ensures balanced muscle distribution across your sessions.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Why is recovery as important as training?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Muscles repair and grow stronger during rest. Without adequate recovery, you risk overtraining and injury. AIVancePro analyzes your workload and alerts you if your volume is too high.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Is strength training safe for beginners?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, as long as you maintain proper technique and progress gradually. AIVancePro offers beginner-friendly exercises with detailed instructions to minimize risk.</div></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

