                <h3 class="faq-subcategory-title">Getting Lean &amp; Defined</h3>
                <div class="faq-list">
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What type of training is best for getting lean?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">A mix of weight training (to preserve muscle mass) and cardio/HIIT (to increase calorie burn) is ideal. The AI coach creates balanced programs for this goal.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Do I need cardio to get lean?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Cardio helps create a calorie deficit, but it is not mandatory. Nutrition plays a more important role. Cardio is an additional tool that the AI coach can integrate into your program.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What role do reps and sets play in getting lean?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">During a cut, maintaining heavy weights with moderate reps (6-12) helps preserve muscle mass. Increasing reps with lighter weights can add a caloric effect, but should not replace heavy work.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Can you get lean with bodyweight exercises?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes, high-intensity bodyweight exercises (burpees, push-ups, jump squats...) are very effective for burning calories. AIVancePro can generate equipment-free HIIT circuits.</div></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="faq-subcategory-title">Building Muscle &amp; Getting Stronger</h3>
                <div class="faq-list">
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            How does AIVancePro help build muscle?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">The AI generates hypertrophy programs with the right volume, intensity and frequency. It tracks your progress and adjusts loads to ensure optimal progressive overload.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            What is the best split for building muscle?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">It depends on your availability. Push/Pull/Legs, Upper/Lower or Full Body are all effective. The AI coach recommends the optimal split based on your training days.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            How long does it take to see results?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
                        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Initial strength gains can be felt within 2-3 weeks. Visible physical changes typically appear after 6 to 8 weeks of consistent training. AIVancePro helps you visualize this progress.</div></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                            Do I need supplements to build muscle?
                            <span class="faq-icon"></span>
                        </button>
